<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/222.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Honduras</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-16"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Acknowledging your gratifying telegram of the 13th, reporting the
                            friendly conference at Amapala, at which it was agreed to consider all
                            differences among the Governments of Honduras, Nicaragua, and Salvador
                            at an end, I have the pleasure to assure you of the cordial appreciation
                            of the Government and people of the United States of anything that may
                            tend to the development of peaceable and mutually beneficial conditions
                            in the neighboring Central American States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>